{"data":[{"name":"94:1","price":"Have We not reassured your heart for you [O Prophet][1],","arabic":"أَلَمۡ نَشۡرَحۡ لَكَ صَدۡرَكَ","category":["94 (Ash-Sharh)","Ash-Sharh","Surah Ash-Sharh"],"ayahNumber":6091,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"[1] i.e., enlighten and gladden your heart for receiving the revelation.","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"alam nashraḥ laka ṣadraka ","translations":["Have not","We expanded","for you","your breast","(1)"],"transliterationArr":["alam","nashraḥ","laka","ṣadraka",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,750],[2,750,1500],[3,1500,1960],[4,1960,3515]]}},{"name":"94:2","price":"and relieved you of your burden[2]","arabic":"وَوَضَعۡنَا عَنكَ وِزۡرَكَ","category":["94 (Ash-Sharh)","Ash-Sharh","Surah Ash-Sharh"],"ayahNumber":6092,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"[2] forgave your previous or future errors, or relieved you of the anxiety you experienced at the beginning of your mission.","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wawaḍaʿnā ʿanka wiz'raka ","translations":["And We removed","from you","your burden","(2)"],"transliterationArr":["wawaḍaʿnā","ʿanka","wiz'raka",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1350],[2,1350,2970],[3,2970,4315]]}},{"name":"94:3","price":"that weighed down your back,","arabic":"ٱلَّذِيٓ أَنقَضَ ظَهۡرَكَ","category":["94 (Ash-Sharh)","Ash-Sharh","Surah Ash-Sharh"],"ayahNumber":6093,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"alladhī anqaḍa ẓahraka ","translations":["Which","weighed upon","your back","(3)"],"transliterationArr":["alladhī","anqaḍa","ẓahraka",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,2700],[2,2700,4140],[3,4140,5465]]}},{"name":"94:4","price":"and raised high your fame for you[3]?","arabic":"وَرَفَعۡنَا لَكَ ذِكۡرَكَ","category":["94 (Ash-Sharh)","Ash-Sharh","Surah Ash-Sharh"],"ayahNumber":6094,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"[3] Allah raised the Prophet's name in numerous ways, such as his name is mentioned twice in the call to prayer five times a day, as well the second call to prayer; at the end of each of the five daily prayers; believers invoke Allah’s blessings upon him and his family; and upon reverting to Islam, his name is mentioned, etc.","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"warafaʿnā laka dhik'raka ","translations":["And We raised high","for you","your reputation","(4)"],"transliterationArr":["warafaʿnā","laka","dhik'raka",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1410],[2,1410,1830],[3,1830,3465]]}},{"name":"94:5","price":"For indeed, with hardship comes ease[4],","arabic":"فَإِنَّ مَعَ ٱلۡعُسۡرِ يُسۡرًا","category":["94 (Ash-Sharh)","Ash-Sharh","Surah Ash-Sharh"],"ayahNumber":6095,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"[4] In Arabic grammar, if a definite noun is repeated, it is referring to the same thing. However, if an indefinite noun is repeated, it is referring to two different things. So here in this and the coming verse they refer to one hardship (a definite noun) and two eases (an indefinite noun), which manifests Allah's favors upon His servants even in times of hardships.","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"fa-inna maʿa al-ʿus'ri yus'ran ","translations":["So indeed","with","the hardship","(is) ease","(5)"],"transliterationArr":["fa-inna","maʿa","al-ʿus'ri","yus'ran",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1640],[2,1640,2010],[3,2010,2850],[4,2850,4445]]}},{"name":"94:6","price":"indeed, with hardship comes ease.","arabic":"إِنَّ مَعَ ٱلۡعُسۡرِ يُسۡرٗا","category":["94 (Ash-Sharh)","Ash-Sharh","Surah Ash-Sharh"],"ayahNumber":6096,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"inna maʿa al-ʿus'ri yus'ran ","translations":["Indeed","with","the hardship","(is) ease","(6)"],"transliterationArr":["inna","maʿa","al-ʿus'ri","yus'ran",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1400],[2,1400,1780],[3,1780,2650],[4,2650,4125]]}},{"name":"94:7","price":"So whenever you are free[5], strive in worship,","arabic":"فَإِذَا فَرَغۡتَ فَٱنصَبۡ","category":["94 (Ash-Sharh)","Ash-Sharh","Surah Ash-Sharh"],"ayahNumber":6097,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"[5] Of your duties.","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"fa-idhā faraghta fa-inṣab ","translations":["So when","you have finished","then labor hard","(7)"],"transliterationArr":["fa-idhā","faraghta","fa-inṣab",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,850],[2,850,1730],[3,1730,3565]]}},{"name":"94:8","price":"and turn to your Lord in devotion.","arabic":"وَإِلَىٰ رَبِّكَ فَٱرۡغَب","category":["94 (Ash-Sharh)","Ash-Sharh","Surah Ash-Sharh"],"ayahNumber":6098,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wa-ilā rabbika fa-ir'ghab ","translations":["And to","your Lord","turn your attention","(8)"],"transliterationArr":["wa-ilā","rabbika","fa-ir'ghab",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,860],[2,860,1740],[3,1740,4125]]}}],"chapter":["94 (Ash-Sharh)","Ash-Sharh","Surah Ash-Sharh","Chapter Ash-Sharh","Sharh","Surah Sharh","Chapter Sharh","Ash Sharh","Surah Ash Sharh","Chapter Ash Sharh","Surah 94","Chapter 94","The Relief","الشرح"],"version":{"key":"english_rwwad","direction":"ltr","language_iso_code":"en","version":"1.0.15","last_update":1711763763,"title":"English Translation - Rowwad Translation Center","description":"Translation of the Quran meanings into Englsih by Rowwad Translation Center in cooperation with Islamhouse.com"}}